text: Jerry Relph (September 4, 1944 âˆ’ December 18, 2020) was an American politician. He was a member of the Republican Party. Relph was born in Boston, Massachusetts. Relph was a member of the Minnesota Senate from 2017 until his death. Relph died on December 18, 2020 in St. Cloud, Minnesota from COVID-19 at the age of 76. ==References== Category:1944 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in the United States Category:State legislators of the United States Category:Politicians from Boston Category:Politicians from Minnesota Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
